The \sn{ASCII} code we will introduce here is one of the first standardized and widely  
used character encodings for a complete alphabet. It is still widely used today. The  
code tries to strike a balance between being able to encode a large set of  
\sns{character?character} and the representational capabilities in the time of punch  
cards (see below).  
    {nparagraph}  

