File: [courses/Jacobs/GenCS/course]{xml/snip/intro.en}]  
 {document}  
 {sparagraph}  
\usemodule{www/slides?browser-rendering-pipeline}  
We have seen that many of the technologies that deal with marked-up documents utilize  
the tree-like structure of (the \sn{DOM}) of \sn{html?HTML} documents. Indeed, it is  
possible to abstract from the concrete vocabulary of \sn{html?HTML} that implements the  
intended layout of hypertexts and the function of its fragments, and build a generic  
framework for document trees. This is what we will study in this \currentsectionlevel.  
    {sparagraph}  
    {document}  


